<body>
    <h1>My top 5 reads of 2022</h1>
    <p>The year of 2022 was the year I finally found my way back to reading.
        <br>A total of 40 books was read and these 5 (in no particular order)
        were all five stare rated.
    </p>


    <h3>IT ENDS WITH US</h3>
    <p>by Colleen Hoover</p>
    <p>
        <em>A heartbreaking and hopeful lovestory about Lily
            <br>and the secrets she unconvers about her big love, Rhys.
            <br>Maybe her first love Atlas was THE one after all?</em>
    </p>


    <h3>MALMA STATION</h3>
    <p>by Alex Schulman</p>
    <p>
        <em>Five people are sitting on a train to the same destination.
            <br>None of them are sure why it has to be this
            destination
            <br>but they know that they will find their truths once they arrive.</em>
    </p>


    <h3>IN FIVE YEARS</h3>
    <p>by Rebecca Serle</p>
    <p>
        <em>Dannie wakes up one day to find herself five years ahead in the future.
            <br>She meets a nice man and get a
            glimpse of their life togheter but <br>suddenly wakes up in the real world. Just a dream?
            <br>Five years pass and
            suddenly the same man from her dreams <br>shows up in her real life.</em>
    </p>


    <h3>EN ENKEL TILL INDIEN</h3>
    <p>by Cassandra Brunstedt</p>
    <p>
        <em>Ella has the life of her dreams.
            <br>But suddenly her perfect life falls apart and she finds herself sitting
            <br>on the plane to a remote
            mountain in India.
            <br>What happens when all you thought you ever wanted
            <br>actually turns out to be exactly what
            you don't need?</em>
    </p>


    <h3>THE ICKABOG</h3>
    <p>by J.K. Rowling</p>
    <p>
        <em>A classic fairytale written by the one and only J.K. Rowling.
            <br>A forgotten story from the authour herself that
            came to
            <br>life during covid when she found it hidden in her house.
            <br>It tells the story about "The Ickabog", a
            monster that hides
            <br>in the North and is responsible for vanishing people and sheeps.
            <br>A tale the villagers
            tells the children to keep them off the mystic forests.</em>
    </p>

</body>

